enton, Maine|Trenton]])<ref name=\"HayesEndorsed2\">{{Cite tweet |number=1042468246333652993 |user=AnthonyEmerso14 |title=Terry Hayes unveils six new endorsements from former state legislators #mepolitics |author=Emerson, Anthony |date=September 19, 2018}}</ref>\n* Leslie Fossel, former state representative (R\u2013[[Alna, Maine|Alna]])<ref name=Hayesendorsed/>\n* Martin Grohman, state representative (I\u2013[[Biddeford, Maine|Biddeford]])<ref name=\"HayesEndorsed3\"/>\n* [[Denise Harlow]], state representative (I\u2013[[Portland, Maine|Portland]])<ref name=Hayesendorsed/>\n* Norm Higgins, state representative (I\u2013[[Dover-Foxcroft, Maine|Dover-Foxcroft]])<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hayesformaine.com/180118 |title=Rep. Norm Higgins Endorses Hayes |date=January 18, 2018 |website=Hayes for Maine |access-date=January 20, 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Bryan Kaenrath]], former state representative (D\u2013[[South Portland, Maine|South Portland]])<ref name=Hayesendorsed/>\n* Gary Knight, former state representative (R\u2013[[Livermore Falls]])<ref name=\"HayesEndorsed2\"/>\n* Leila J. Percy, former state representative (D\u2013[[Phippsburg]])<ref name=\"HayesEndorsed2\"/>\n* Stanley Short, former state representative (D\u2013[[Pittsfield, Maine|Pittsfield]])<ref name=Hayesendorsed/>\n* [[Ed Suslovic]], former [[Mayor of Portland, Maine|Mayor of Portland]] and former state representative (D\u2013[[Portland, Maine|Portland]])<ref name=\"HayesEndorsed3\"/>\n* [[Windol Weaver]], former state representative (R-[[York, Maine|York]])<ref name=\"HayesEndorsed2\"/>\n\n; Individuals\n* Eliot Cutler, attorney and independent candidate for governor ([[Maine gubernatorial election, 2010|2010]] and [[Maine gubernatorial election, 2014|2014]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bangordailynews.com/2017/05/02/politics/eliot-cutler-is-recruiting-independents-to-run-for-the-maine-legislature/?ref=topStories4Thumb|title=Eliot Cutler is recruiting independents to run for the Maine Legislature|work=[[Bangor Daily News]]|last=Shepherd|first=Michael|date=May 2, 2017|accessdate=May 3, 2017}}</ref>\n\n; Organizations\n* [[Unite America]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ivn.us/2017/05/24/centrist-project-announces-first-independent-endorsement-2018/|title=Centrist Project Sees Opportunity in Maine to Disrupt Two-Party Duopoly - IVN.us|date=May 24, 2017|publisher=}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Endorsements box\n| title = Janet Mills (D)\n| list =\n; National politicians\n* '''[[Joe Biden]], former [[Vice President of the United States]]'''<ref>{{Cite tweet | number= 1057287392120500234 | user=JanetMillsforME | title= I am thrilled to have the support of @JoeBiden, a champion for working people around the country. Our campaign is focused on taking Maine in a new direction that always puts hardworking Mainers first. I can think of no better supporter of that cause than Vice President Biden. | date=October 30, 2018}}</ref>\n* '''[[Susan Rice]], former [[United States Ambassador to the United Nations]] and former [[United States National Security Advisor|National Security Advisor]]'''<ref>{{Cite tweet |number= 1050891769100025857 |user=mikeshepherdME |title=Just confirmed: @AmbassadorRice was at a @JanetMillsforME fundraiser tonight in Rockport, per @swogden10. #mepolitics |author=Shepherd, Michael |date=October 12, 2018}}</ref>\n; Local and statewide politicians\n* '''[[Justin Alfond]], former [[President of the Maine Senate]]'''<ref name=\"MillsBaysideBowl\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.janetmills.com/baysidebowl |title=JOIN US AT BAYSIDE BOWL! |date=October 17, 2018 |access-date=October 18, 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Joseph E. Brennan]], former governor of Maine ([[Maine gubernatorial election, 1978|1979]]\u2013[[Maine gubernatorial election, 1982|1987]]), former US Representative for [[Maine's 1st congressional district]] (1987\u20131991), former [[Maine Attorney General]] (1975-1979), nominee for Governor in [[Maine gubernatorial election, 1990|1990]] and [[Maine gubernatorial election, 1994|1994]], 