erald]] |access-date=October 23, 2018}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Endorsements box\n| title = Shawn Moody (R)\n| list =\n; State and local politicians\n* [[Richard A. Bennett|Rick Bennett]], former [[President of the Maine Senate]], former Chair of the Maine Republican Party<ref name=\"RBennett\"/>\n* '''[[Ken Fredette]], State House Minority Leader, 2018 gubernatorial candidate'''<ref name=\"GOPUnity\"/>\n* '''[[Garrett Mason]], State Senate Majority Leader, 2018 gubernatorial candidate'''<ref name=\"GOPUnity\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.pressherald.com/2018/06/19/moody-rallies-republicans-at-the-state-house-following-primary-election/ |title=Shawn Moody tells Republicans at rally he\u2019d carry on LePage\u2019s legacy |last=Thistle |first=Scott |date=June 19, 2018 |work=[[Portland Press Herald]] |access-date=July 19, 2018}}</ref>\n* '''[[Mary Mayhew]], former Director the Maine Department of Health and Human Services'''<ref name=\"GOPUnity\"/>\n* '''[[Mike Thibodeau]], [[President of the Maine Senate]], 2018 gubernatorial candidate'''<ref name=\"GOPUnity\"/>\n* '''[[Paul LePage]], [[Governor of Maine]]'''<ref name=\"GOPUnity\"/>\n\n;Other individuals\n* Adrienne Bennett, former spokesperson for Governor [[Paul LePage]]<ref name=\"ABennett\"/>\n* '''[[Matt DiBenedetto]], [[NASCAR]] driver'''<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://wgme.com/news/local/shawn-moody-unveils-new-advertisement-on-nascar-vehicle |title=Shawn Moody unveils new advertisement on NASCAR vehicle |last=WGME |date=July 18, 2018 |work=[[WGME-TV]] |access-date=July 19, 2018}}</ref>\n* Ann LePage, First Lady of Maine<ref name=\"FirstLady\"/>\n* Aaron D. Chadbourne, writer and activist, former write-in candidate for Governor<ref name=\"Chadbourne\"/>\n\n; Organizations\n* '''[[Associated Builders and Contractors]] of Maine'''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bangordailynews.com/bdn-maine/community/associated-builders-and-contractors-of-maine-announces-endorsement-of-shawn-moody-for-governor/|title=Associated Builders and Contractors of Maine Announces Endorsement of Shawn Moody for Governor|work=[[Bangor Daily News]]|date=June 28, 2018}}</ref>\n* '''Sportman's Alliance of Maine'''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://waldo.villagesoup.com/p/sportsmans-alliance-endorses-moody/1778187|title=Sportsman's Alliance endorses Moody|website=waldo.villagesoup.com|publisher=The Republican Journal|date=September 10, 2018}}</ref>\n}}\n\n=== Debates ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! Dates\n! Location\n! Mills\n! Moody\n! Hayes\n! Caron\n! Link\n|-\n|October 10, 2018\n|[[Portland, Maine|Portland]], [[Maine]]\n|Participant\n|Participant\n|Participant\n|Participant\n| align=left | [https://www.c-span.org/video/?453424-1/maine-gubernatorial-debate Full debate] - [[C-SPAN]]\n|-\n|October 25, 2018\n|[[Augusta, Maine|Augusta]], [[Maine]]\n|Participant\n|Participant\n|Participant\n|Participant\n| align=left | [https://www.c-span.org/video/?453645-1/maine-gubernatorial-debate Full debate] - [[C-SPAN]]\n\n|}\n\n===Polling===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%\n|- valign=bottom\n! Poll source\n! Date(s)<br>administered\n! Sample<br>size\n! Margin<br>of error\n! style=\"width:75px;\"| Shawn<br>Moody (R)\n! style=\"width:75px;\"| Janet<br>Mills (D)\n! style=\"width:75px;\"| Terry<br>Hayes (I)\n! style=\"width:75px;\"| Alan<br>Caron (I)\n! Other\n! Undecided\n|-\n| [https://projects.fivethirtyeight.com/polls/20181102_ME_G.pdf Slingshot Strategies (I-Hayes)]\n| align=center| November 1, 2018\n| align=center| 518\n| align=center| \u2013\n| align=center| 38%\n| {{party shading/Democratic}} align=center| '''55%'''\n| align=center| 7%\n| align=center| \u2013\n| align=center| \u2013\n| align=center| \u2013\n|-\n| [https://www.emerson.edu/news-events/emerson-college-today/emerson-polls-ct-me-nh-two-house-races-play-potential-gubernatorial-upset Emerson College]\n| align=center| October 27\u201329, 2018\n| align=center| 883\n| align=center| \u00b1 3.5%\n| align=center| 42%\n| {{party shading/Democratic}} align=center| '''50%'''\n| align=center| \u2013\n| align=center| \u2013\n| align=center| 5%\n| align=center| 4%\n|-\n| [https://www.realclearpolitics.com/docs/Pan_Atlantic_Research_Maine.pdf Pan Atlantic Research]\n| align=center| October 1\u20137, 2018\n| align=center| 500\n| align=center| \u00b1 4.4%\n| align=center| 36%\n| {{party shading/Democratic}} align=center| '''44%'''\n| align=center| 8%\n| align=center| 2%\n| align=center| \u2013\n| align=center| 10%\n|-\n| [https://medium.com/@ChngRsrch/50-of-mainers-less-likely-to-re-elect-senator-collins-if-she-votes-to-confirm-kavanaugh-2d0ab56a6f3b Change Research]\n| align=center| September 30 \u2013 October 1, 2018\n| align=center| 801\n| align=center| \u2013\n| align=center| 44%\n| {{party shading/Democratic}} align=center| '''52%'''\n| align=center| \u2013\n| align=center| \u2013\n| align=center| \u2013\n| align=center| \u2013\n|-\n| [https://www.scribd.com/document/390840892/Hayes-Poll-Findings-Memo-10-14-18?secret_password=egwz2WYfOa0o3C1DXt4j Slingshot Strategies (I-Hayes)]\n| align=center| September 26\u201330, 2018\n| align=center| 600\n| align=center| \u2013\n| align=center| 33%\n| {{party shading/Democratic}} align=center| '''41%'''\n| align=center| 10%\n| align=center| 2%\n| align=center| 0%\n| align=center| 13%\n|-\n| [https://www.suffolk.edu/documents/SUPRC/8_8_2018_marginals.pdf Suffolk University]\n| align=center| August 2\u20136, 2018\n| align=center| 500\n| align=center| \u00b1 4.4%\n| align=center| '''39%'''\n| align=center| '''39%'''\n| align=center| 4%\n| align=center| 3%\n| align=center| \u2013\n| align=center| 16%\n|}\n\n<!-- = = = don't edit next six lines for Navbox below = = = -->\n{| class=\"navbox collapsible collapsed\" style=\"text-align:left; border:0; margin-top:0.2em;\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:#cff; font-weight:normal;\"|\n'''Hypothetical polling'''\n|-\n| style=\"border:solid 1px silver; padding:8px; background:white;\"|\n<!-- = = = don't edit above six lines = = =  -->\n;