, 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Mark Dion (politician)|Mark Dion]], state senator and former [[Cumberland County, Maine|Cumberland County]] Sheriff<ref>{{cite news|url=http://bangordailynews.com/2017/10/12/politics/former-maine-sheriff-enters-race-for-governor-as-a-democrat/|title=Former Maine sheriff enters race for governor as a Democrat|last=Cousins|first=Christopher|date=October 12, 2017|work=[[Bangor Daily News]]|accessdate=October 12, 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Mark Eves]], former [[Speaker of the Maine House of Representatives]]<ref name=\"EvesAnnouncement\">{{cite news|url=http://bangordailynews.com/2017/07/13/politics/democrat-mark-eves-launches-maine-gubernatorial-run/|title=Ex-speaker Mark Eves launches Maine gubernatorial run|last=Cousins|first=Christopher|date=July 13, 2017|work=[[Bangor Daily News]]|accessdate=July 13, 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Diane Russell]], former state representative<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pressherald.com/2017/08/10/former-portland-rep-diane-russell-joins-governors-race/|title=Former Portland state Rep. Diane Russell joins governor's race|date=August 10, 2017|publisher=}}</ref>\n* Betsy Sweet, former director of the [[Maine Women's Lobby]]<ref name=sweet>{{cite web|url=http://www.pressherald.com/2017/05/30/progressive-activist-betsy-sweet-announces-bid-for-maine-governor//|title=Progressive Activist Betsy Sweet announces bid for Maine governor- |publisher=Portland Press Herald |author=Kevin Miller |date=May 30, 2017 |accessdate=May 30, 2017}}</ref>\n\n====Failed to make ballot====\n* Dominic A. Crocitto<ref>{{cite web |url=https://secure.mainecampaignfinance.com/#/exploreDetails/5752/10/null/32/2018 |title=Filings for Dominic Anthony Crocitto |date=December 19, 2017 |website=Maine Commission on Governmental Ethics and Election Practices |access-date=January 18, 2018}}</ref>\n* Steve DeAngelis, schoolteacher<ref>{{cite news|url=http://bangordailynews.com/2017/12/04/uncategorized/collins-support-for-gop-tax-bill-could-waver-if-trump-mcconnell-cant-keep-p