enhart, former gubernatorial candidate (2018)<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.markevesforme.com/news/patrick-eisenhart-drops-democratic-gubernatorial-primary-endorses-eves-campaign/ |title=Patrick Eisenhart Drops Out of Democratic Gubernatorial Primary, Endorses Eves Campaign |date=March 6, 2018 |work=MarkEvesForME.com}}</ref>\n* [[Sean Faircloth]], [[Bangor, Maine|Bangor]] City Councillor, former Mayor of Bangor, former state senator, former gubernatorial candidate (2018)<ref name=\"EvesEndorsements\"/>\n* [[Richard Farnsworth (politician)|Richard Farnsworth]], state representative<ref name=\"EvesEndorsements\"/>\n* [[Ryan Fecteau]], state representative<ref name=\"EvesEndorsements\"/>\n* [[Roger Fuller]], state representative<ref name=\"EvesEndorsements\"/>\n* [[Drew Gattine]], state representative<ref name=\"EvesEndorsements\"/>\n* [[Anne Haskell]], former state senator<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.pressherald.com/2018/04/13/letter-to-the-editor-maine-needs-champion-of-the-needy-so-choose-mark-eves-for-governor/ |title=Letter to the editor: Maine needs champion of the needy, so choose Mark Eves for governor |last=Haskell |first=Anne |date=April 13, 2018 |work=[[Portland Press Herald]] |access-date=April 19, 2018}}</ref>\n* Erik Jorgensen, state representative<ref name=\"EvesEndorsements\"/>\n* Chuck Kruger, former state representative<ref name=\"EvesEndorsements\"/>\n* Thomas Longstaff, state representative<ref name=\"EvesEndorsements\"/>\n* Louis Luchini, state representative<ref name=\"EvesEndorsements\"/>\n* Jay McCreight, state representative<ref name=\"EvesEndorsements\"/>\n* Jennifer Ellen Parker, state representative<ref name=\"EvesEndorsements\"/>\n* [[Deane Rykerson]], state representative<ref name=\"EvesEndorsements\"/>\n* [[Linda Sanborn]], former state representative<ref name=\"EvesEndorsements\"/>\n* John Alden Spear, state representative<ref name=\"EvesEndorsements\"/>\n* Ben Sprague, Mayor of Bangor<ref name=\"EvesEndorsements\"/>\n* [[Joan Welsh]], former state representative<ref name=\"EvesEndorsements\"/>\n; Individuals\n* Adam Lee, small business owner and environmental activist<ref name=\"EvesEndorsements\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.markevesforme.com/news/adam-lee-endorses-mark-eves-governor/ |title=Adam Lee Endorses Mark Eves for Governor |date=March 1, 2018 |work=MarkEvesForME.com}}</ref>\n* [[Warren Silver]], former [[Maine Supreme Judicial Court]] justice<ref name=\"EvesEndorsements\"/>\n; Organizations\n* Iron Workers Local 7<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://fiddleheadfocus.com/2018/05/03/uncategorized/iron-workers-union-endorses-mark-eves-for-governor/ |title=Iron Workers union endorses Mark Eves for governor |date=May 3, 2018 |work=Fiddlehead Focus}}</ref>\n* [[Working Families Party]]<ref name=\"WFPVideo\">{{Cite video |url=https://www.facebook.com/WorkingFamilies/videos/10156098975456418/?hc_ref=ARR2D9twEiewnDKN56bnK1GKKsu5oYBsuC53bTrVa6a5z4XGL5f7Ct3L8JR5ZjvBku0 |title=Maine has three progressive candidates for Governor and a brand new voting system. |date=June 5, 2018 |last=Working Families Party}}</ref> (also endorsed Sweet and Russell)\n}}\n{{Endorsements box\n| title = Janet Mills\n| list =\n; Local and statewide politicians\n* [[Joseph E. Brennan]], former governor of Maine ([[Maine gubernatorial election, 1978|1979]]\u2013[[Maine gubernatorial election, 1982|1987]]), former US Representative for [[Maine's 1st congressional district]] (1987\u20131991), former [[Maine Attorney General]] (1975-1979), nominee for Governor in [[Maine gubernatorial election, 1990|1990]] and [[Maine gubernatorial election, 1994|1994]], nominee for US Senate in [[United States Senate election in Maine, 1996|1996]], candidate for Governor in [[Maine gubernatorial election, 1974|1974]]<ref name=\"Brennan\">{{cite tweet |number= 1002224670157008896 |user= JanetMillsforME |author=Janet Mills |title= I'm honored to have the endorsement of former AG and Governor, Joe Brennan. \"A lifelong Democrat, a founder of the 