ed States House of Representatives elections in Maine, 2008|2008]]<ref>{{cite tweet |author=Anthony Emerson |user= AnthonyEmerso14|number=996822164551688192 |date=May 16, 2018 |title=Portland mayor Ethan Strimling (@mayorstrim) endorses Betsy Sweet (@Sweet4Governor) in email to Sweet supporters ahead of this weekend's Democratic Convention. #mepolitics}}</ref>\n* [[Michael Sylvester (politician)|Mike Sylvester]], state representative<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.facebook.com/sylvester.forstatehouse/posts/543012886092791 |title=Proud to be with these folks... |last=Sylvester |first=Mike |date=June 5, 2018 |website=Facebook |access-date=June 11, 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Charlotte Warren]], state representative<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.facebook.com/photo.php?fbid=10213860695004127&set=a.1177296225157.2028784.1010665700&type=3&theater |title=Team Sweet! Just imagine how SWEET it could be! \u2014 with Alex Michaud, Betsy Sweet and Nasreen Yousef at Public Market House - from Charlotte Warren |last=Warren |first=Charlotte |date=April 27, 2018 |website=Facebook}}</ref>\n* Barb Wood, former [[Portland, Maine|Portland]] [[Portland, Maine City Council|City Councillor]], vice president of the [[Equality Maine]] Foundation<ref name=\"WoodAndMcCormick\">{{Cite tweet |number=1005641731612831745 |user=AnthonyEmerso14 |title=Former Portland City Councillor and current VP of @EqualityMaine Foundation Barb Wood endorses Betsy Sweet (@Sweet4Governor) #mepolitics |author=Anthony Emerson |date=June 9, 2018}}</ref>\n\n; Other individuals\n* [[Ben Cohen (businessman)|Ben Cohen]], cofounder, [[Ben & Jerry's]]<ref name=\"SweetMailers\"/>\n* [[Cenk Uygur]], journalist, host of ''The Young Turks''<ref>{{Cite video |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UrvpJmokzr4 |title=Maine Activist Vows To Protect Water And Native Tribes |date=February 23, 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Marianne Williamson]], writer<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://sistergiant.com/2018-endorsements-2/ |title=2018 endorsements |last=Williamson |first=Marianne |website=SisterGiant.com}}</ref>\n\n; Organizations\n* Southern Maine [[Democratic Socialists of America]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://southernmainedsa.org/2018/04/12/press-release-southern-maine-dsa-endorses-betsy-sweet-in-june-primary-for-maine-state-governor/ |title=Press Release: Southern Maine DSA Endorses Betsy Sweet in June primary for Maine State Governor |last=Sykes |first=Kate |date=April 12, 2018 |website=SouthernMaineDSA.org |access-date=April 15, 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Working Families Party]]<ref name=\"SweetMailers\"/><ref name=\"WFPVideo\"/> (also endorsed Eves and Russell)\n}}\n\n===Polling===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%\n|- valign=bottom\n! Poll source\n! Date(s)<br>administered\n! Sample<br>size\n! Margin<br>of error\n! RCV<br>round\n! style=\"width:75px;\"| Adam<br>Cote\n! style=\"width:75px;\"| Donna<br>Dion\n! style=\"width:75px;\"| Mark<br>Dion\n! style=\"width:75px;\"| Mark<br>Eves\n! style=\"width:75px;\"| Janet<br>Mills\n! style=\"width:75px;\"| Diane<br>Russell\n! style=\"width:75px;\"| Betsy<br>Sweet\n! Undecided\n|-\n| rowspan=5| [http://bangordailynews.com/2018/05/06/politics/poll-moody-mills-are-front-runners-in-maines-unsettled-june-primaries/ SurveyUSA]\n| align=center rowspan=5| April 26 \u2013 May 1, 2018\n| align=center rowspan=5| 649\n| align=center rowspan=5| \u00b1 4.2%\n| align=center| Round 1\n| align=center| 9%\n| align=center| 2%\n| align=center| 10%\n| align=center| 16%\n| align=center| 32%\n| align=center| 4%\n| align=center| 5%\n| align=center| 24%\n|-\n| align=center| Round 2\n| align=center| 13%\n| align=center| \u2013\n| align=center| 13%\n| align=center| 20%\n| align=center| 42%\n| align=center| 5%\n| align=center| 6%\n| align=center rowspan=4|\n|-\n| align=center| Round 3\n| align=center| 13%\n| align=center| \u2013\n| align=center| 13%\n| align=center| 22%\n| align=center| 43%\n| align=center| \u2013\n| align=center| 8%\n|-\n| align=center| Round 4\n| align=center| 14%\n| align=cente