e tweet | number= 1057287392120500234 | user=JanetMillsforME | title= I am thrilled to have the support of @JoeBiden, a champion for working people around the country. Our campaign is focused on taking Maine in a new direction that always puts hardworking Mainers first. I can think of no better supporter of that cause than Vice President Biden. | date=October 30, 2018}}</ref>\n* '''[[Susan Rice]], former [[United States Ambassador to the United Nations]] and former [[United States National Security Advisor|National Security Advisor]]'''<ref>{{Cite tweet |number= 1050891769100025857 |user=mikeshepherdME |title=Just confirmed: @AmbassadorRice was at a @JanetMillsforME fundraiser tonight in Rockport, per @swogden10. #mepolitics |author=Shepherd, Michael |date=October 12, 2018}}</ref>\n; Local and statewide politicians\n* '''[[Justin Alfond]], former [[President of the Maine Senate]]'''<ref name=\"MillsBaysideBowl\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.janetmills.com/baysidebowl |title=JOIN US AT BAYSIDE BOWL! |date=October 17, 2018 |access-date=October 18, 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Joseph E. Brennan]], former governor of Maine ([[Maine gubernatorial election, 1978|1979]]\u2013[[Maine gubernatorial election, 1982|1987]]), former US Representative for [[Maine's 1st congressional district]] (1987\u20131991), former [[Maine Attorney General]] (1975-1979), nominee for Governor in [[Maine gubernatorial election, 1990|1990]] and [[Maine gubernatorial election, 1994|1994]], nominee for US Senate in [[United States Senate election in Maine, 1996|1996]], candidate for Governor in [[Maine gubernatorial election, 1974|1974]]<ref name=\"Brennan\"/>\n* [[Lynn Bromley]], former state senator<ref name=\"Bromley\"/>\n* [[Emily Cain]], former state senator, nominee for [[Maine's 2nd congressional district|ME-02]] in 2014 and 2016, executive director of [[EMILY's List]]<ref name=\"MillsRally\"/>\n* '''Alan Caron, 2018 gubernatorial candidate'''<ref name=\"CaronEndorse\"/>\n* '''Adam Cote, 2018 gubernator