1]]\n*[[3rdeyegirl]]\n*[[4Minute]]\n*[[Agalloch]]\n*[[Allo Darlin']]\n*[[Aiden]]\n*[[Bane (band)|Bane]]\n*[[Blood on the Dance Floor (duo)|Blood on the Dance Floor]]\n*[[Bolt Thrower]]\n*[[Boom Boom Satellites]]\n*[[Crosby, Stills, Nash & Young]]<ref>{{cite web|last1=Young|first1=Alex|title=Crosby, Stills, and Nash have broken up|url=http://consequenceofsound.net/2016/03/crosby-stills-and-nash-have-broken-up/|website=Consequence of Sound|accessdate=March 9, 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Dead or Alive (band)|Dead or Alive]]\n*[[Dream (American group)|Dream]]\n*[[Eagles (band)|Eagles]]\n*[[Empire! Empire! (I Was a Lonely Estate)]]\n*[[The Enemy (UK rock band)|The Enemy]]\n*[[Fearless Vampire Killers (band)|Fearless Vampire Killers]]\n*[[Finch (American band)|Finch]]\n*[[For Today]]\n*[[Funeral for a Friend]]\n*[[FVK (band)|FVK]]\n*[[Giant Sand]]\n*[[Trans Day of Revenge|G.L.O.S.S.]]\n*[[Gnashing of Teeth]]\n*[[Gossip (band)|Gossip]]\n*[[Graveyard (band)|Graveyard]]\n*[[I, the Breather]]\n*[[Jack \u00dc]]\n*[[Joey + Rory]]\n*[[Sharon Jones & The Dap-Kings]]\n*[[La Ley (band)|La Ley]]\n*[[A Lighter Shade of Brown]]\n*[[Lionheart (Hardcore punk band)|Lionheart]]\n*[[Lush (band)|Lush]]\n*[[Majical Cloudz]]\n*[[Marion (band)|Marion]]\n*[[Matchbook Romance]]\n*[[Maybeshewill]]\n*[[Mischief Brew]]\n*[[Motion City Soundtrack]]\n*[[Mudvayne]]\n*[[Nektar]]\n*[[Nomeansno]]\n*[[P.M. Dawn]]\n*[[The Presidents of the United States of America (band)|The Presidents of the United States of America]]\n*[[Rainbow (South Korean band)]]\n*[[Sally Shapiro]]\n*[[Thee Satisfaction]]\n*[[School of Seven Bells]]\n*[[SMAP]]\n*[[Sockweb]]\n*[[Sorry About Dresden]]\n*[[Spirit of the West]]\n*[[The Stooges]]\n*[[Suicide (band)|Suicide]]\n*[[Transit (band)|Transit]]\n*[[Twisted Sister]]\n*[[Viola Beach]]\n*[[Wodensthrone]]\n*[[You, Me, and Everyone We Know]]\n*[[Youth Lagoon]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Deaths==\n===January===\n* '''1'''\n** [[Gilbert Kaplan]], (74), American conductor and businessman, cancer.<ref>[https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/obituaries/12077312/Gilbert-Kaplan-conductor-obituary.html Gilbert Kaplan, conductor \u2013 obituary]</ref>\n** [[Mark B]], (45), British hip-hop record producer.<ref>[http://www.factmag.com/2016/01/01/mark-b-died/ UK hip-hop producer Mark B has died]</ref>\n** [[Gilberto Mendes]], (93), Brazilian composer.<ref>[http://musimid.blogspot.no/2016/01/gilberto-mendes-1922-2016-sailing-in.html Gilberto Mendes (1922\u20132016): Sailing in the Ocean of Creativity]</ref>\n* '''2''' \u2013 [[Rino Salviati]], (93), Italian singer, guitarist and actor.<ref>[http://spettacoliecultura.ilmessaggero.it/musica/rino_salviati_morto_cantautore_roma-1467352.html Roma, addio a Rino Salviati, voce e chitarra di \"Prigioniero di un sogno\"] {{in lang|it}}</ref>\n* '''3'''\n** [[Paul Bley]] (83), Canadian jazz pianist.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/01/06/arts/music/paul-bley-adventurous-jazz-pianist-dies-at-83.html | title=Paul Bley, Adventurous Jazz Pianist, Dies at 83 | first=Ben | last=Ratliff | work=[[The New York Times]] | date=2016-01-05 | accessdate=2016-03-02}}</ref>\n** Jason Mackenroth (46), American rock drummer ([[Rollins Band]], [[Mother Superior (band)|Mother Superior]]), prostate cancer.<ref>[http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/obituary/6835245/jason-mackenroth-rollins-band-drummer-dies-46/ Jason Mackenroth, Former Rollins Band Drummer, Dies at 46]</ref>\n* '''4'''\n** [[Long John Hunter]], (84), American blues guitarist and singer-songwriter.<ref>[http://www.elpasotimes.com/story/news/local/el-paso/2016/01/05/el-paso-music-legend-long-john-hunter-dies/78310304/ El Paso music legend Long John Hunter dies]</ref>\n** [[Achim Mentzel]], (69), German musician and television presenter.<ref>[http://www.dw.com/en/german-entertainer-achim-mentzel-dies-at-69/a-18958351 German entertainer Achim Mentzel dies at 69]</ref>\n*'''5'''\n** [[Pierre Boulez]], (90), French composer and conductor.<ref>[https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/obituaries/12084616/Pierre-Boulez-obituary.html Pierre Boulez \u2013 obituary]</ref>\n**[[Nicholas Caldwell]], (71), American R&B singer ([[The Whispers]]).<ref>[http://www.eurweb.com/2016/01/we-remember-nicholas-nick-caldwell-of-the-whispers-dies-at-71/ We Remember: Nick Caldwell of the Whispers Dies at 71]</ref>\n** [[Hanna-Marie Weydahl]], (93), Norwegian pianist.<ref>[https://snl.no/Hanna-Marie_Weydahl Hanna-Marie Weydahl] {{in lang|no}}</ref>\n* '''7'''\n** [[Kitty Kallen]], (94), American singer (\"[[Little Things Mean a Lot]]\").<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2016/01/08/arts/music/kitty-kallen-big-band-singer-of-besame-mucho-dies-at-94.html?_r=0 Kitty Kallen, Big Band Singer of \u2018B\u00e9same Mucho,\u2019 Dies at 94]</ref>\n** [[Troy Shondell]], (76), American singer, complications from Alzheimer's disease and Parkinson's disease.<ref>[http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/obituary/6836434/troy-shondell-this-time-were-really-breaking-up-dies-at-76 Troy Shondell, Singer of 'This Time (We're Really Breaking Up),' Dies at 76]</ref>\n* '''8'''\n** [[Otis Clay]], (73), American R&B and soul singer (\"[[Tryin' to Live My Life Without You]]\", \"[[The Only Way Is Up]]\"), heart attack.<ref>[http://www.post-gazette.com/news/obituaries/2016/01/09/Soul-legend-Otis-Clay-dies-at-73/stories/201601090143 Soul legend Otis Clay dies at 73]</ref>\n**[[Red Simpson]], (81), American country singer-songwriter (\"[[I'm a Truck]]\"), complications from a heart attack.<ref>[http://www.bakersfield.com/news/breaking-news/2016/01/08/bakersfield-sound-pioneer-red-simpson-dies-at-81.html Bakersfield Sound pioneer Red Simpson dies at 81]</ref>\n**[[Brett Smiley]], (60), American singer-songwriter.<ref>[http://www.heraldnet.com/article/20160111/NEWS02/160119811 Glam rock cult hero Brett Smiley dies in NYC at age 60]</ref>\n* '''10''' \u2013 [[David Bowie]], (69), English songwriter and artist.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/01/11/entertainment/david-bowie-death/index.html | title=David Bowie is dead at 69}}</ref>\n* '''17''' \u2013 [[Carina Jaarnek]] (53), Swedish singer and [[Dansband]] artist (cerebral haemorrhage).<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.aftonbladet.se/nojesbladet/musik/article22103623.ab | title=Dansbandsdrottningen Carina Jaarnek d\u00f6d | language=Swedish | publisher=[[Aftonbladet]] |date=2016-01-17 | accessdate=2016-03-15}}</ref>\n* '''18''' \u2013 [[Glenn Frey]] (67), American guitarist and vocalist ([[The Eagles]]).<ref>[https://www.washingtonpost.com/entertainment/music/glenn-frey-guitarist-for-the-eagles-dies-at-67/2016/01/18/89aee084-be30-11e5-83d4-42e3bceea902_story.html Glenn Frey, guitarist for the Eagles, dies at 67 \u2013 The Washington Post<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>\n* '''25''' \u2013 [[Leif Solberg]] (101), Norwegian composer and organist.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.oa.no/musikk/kultur/lena/komponist-leif-solberg-101-er-dod/s/5-35-226866 |title=Komponist Leif Solberg (101) er d\u00f8d |language=Norwegian |last=Solhaug |first=Espen Amundrud |work=[[Oppland Arbeiderblad]] |date=2016-01-26 |accessdate=2016-03-15 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160126125023/http://www.oa.no/musikk/kultur/lena/komponist-leif-solberg-101-er-dod/s/5-35-226866 |archivedate=2016-01-26 }}</ref>\n* '''26'''\n** [[T.J. Tindall]] (65), American guitarist ([[MFSB]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://rocknycliveandrecorded.com/sad-news-from-the-world-of-philadelphia-soul-guitarist-t-j-tindall-dead.html|title=Friends, Colleagues Remember Guitarist TJ Tindall, Part Of The Musical Foundation Of The Sound Of Philadelphia|access-date=2016-11-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161020040017/http://rocknycliveandrecorded.com/sad-news-from-the-world-of-philadelphia-soul-guitarist-t-j-tindall-dead.html|archive-date=2016-10-20|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n** [[Black (singer)|Black]] (53), Pop/new wave singer-songwriter, Traffic accident\n* '''28'''\n** [[Signe Toly Anderson]] (74), American vocalist ([[Jefferson 