''' \u2013 [[Pauline Oliveros]] (84), American composer\n*'''29''' \u2013 [[Allan Zavod]] (71), Australian keyboardist and composer\n*'''30''' \u2013 [[Ivar Thomassen]] (62), Norwegian folk singer, songwriter, and jazz pianist.<ref>{{cite news |url= http://www.altaposten.no/kultur/2016/11/30/%E2%80%93-En-av-de-store-er-g%C3%A5tt-bort-13864429.ece |title= En av de store er g\u00e5tt bort |language=no |first= Rolf Edmund |last=Lund |newspaper= [[Altaposten]] |date= 30 November 2016 |accessdate= 2016-12-05}}</ref>\n\n===December===\n*'''2''' \u2013 [[Mark Gray (singer)|Mark Gray]] (64), American singer-songwriter ([[Exile (American band)|Exile]])\n*'''4''' \u2013 Ralph Johnson (67), American singer ([[The Impressions]])\n*'''8'''\n** [[Greg Lake]] (69), English progressive-rock vocalist and multi-instrumentalist<ref>[https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/greg-lake-emerson-lake-palmer-co-founder-dead-at-69-w454546 Greg Lake, Emerson, Lake & Palmer Co-Founder, Dead at 69 \u2013 Rolling Stone<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>\n** [[Junaid Jamshed]] (52), Pakistani singer-songwriter ([[Vital Signs (pop band)|Vital Signs]]), flight collision<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2016/dec/07/pakistan-plane-crashes-flight-pk661 Pop star Junaid Jamshed among 48 killed in Pakistan plane crash | World news | The Guardian<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>\n*'''11''' \u2013 Joe Ligon (80), American gospel singer ([[Mighty Clouds of Joy]])\n*'''24''' \u2013 [[Rick Parfitt]] (68), English musician and songwriter ([[Status Quo (band)|Status Quo]])<ref>[https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-28640835 Obituary: Rick Parfitt \u2013 BBC News<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>\n*'''25''' \u2013 [[George Michael]] (53), English singer-songwriter ([[Wham!]]) <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-38432862 |title=Ex-Wham singer George Michael dies |publisher=[[BBC]] |date=25 December 2016 |accessdate=25 December 2016}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n{{Portal|Music}}\n* [[Timel