idth=30em|\n*[[2016 in classical music|Classical]]\n*[[2016 in country music|Country]]\n*[[2016 in electronic music|Electronic]]\n*[[2016 in jazz|Jazz]]\n*[[2016 in Latin music|Latin music]]\n*[[2016 in heavy metal music|Heavy metal]]\n*[[2016 in hip hop music|Hip hop]]\n*[[2016 in opera|Opera]]\n*[[2016 in pop music|Pop]]\n*[[2016 in rock music|Rock]]\n}}\n\n== Albums released ==\n{{main|List of 2016 albums}}\n\n== Significant performances ==\n* [[March 25]] \u2013 British [[rock and roll]] band, [[The Rolling Stones]] become the first foreign rock band to perform in Cuba,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://variety.com/2016/film/reviews/rolling-stones-ole-toronto-1201858075/|title=Toronto Film Review: \u2018The Rolling Stones Ol\u00e9 Ol\u00e9 Ol\u00e9!: A Trip Across Latin America\u2019|last=Barker|first=Andrew|date=2016-09-12|work=Variety|access-date=2017-06-24|language=en-US}}</ref> which was documented in their 2016 concert film, [[The Rolling Stones: Havana Moon]].\n\n== Awards ==\n{{Globalize|section|Western culture|date=August 2018}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! [[58th Annual Grammy Awards]]\n|-\n| {{small|''Record of the Year: [[Uptown Funk]] \u2013 [[Mark Ronson]] featuring [[Bruno Mars]] \u2022 Album of the Year: [[1989 (Taylor Swift album)|1989]] \u2013 [[Taylor Swift]] \u2022 Song of the Year: [[Thinking Out Loud]] \u2013 [[Ed Sheeran]] \u2022 Best New Artist: [[Meghan Trainor]]''}}\n|-\n! [[2016 Billboard Music Awards|Billboard Music Awards]]\n|-\n| {{small|''Artist of the Year: [[Adele]] \u2022 New Artist of the Year: [[Fetty Wap]] \u2022 Top Hot 100 Song: [[See You Again (Wiz Khalifa song)|See You Again]] \u2022 Top Billboard 200 Album: ''[[25 (Adele album)|25]]''}}\n|-\n! [[58th Japan Record Awards]] \n|-\n| {{small|''Grand Prix'': \"Anata no Suki na Tokoro\" ([[:ja:\u3042\u306a\u305f\u306e\u597d\u304d\u306a\u3068\u3053\u308d|ja]]) by [[Kana Nishino]] \u2022 ''Best Singer'': [[Masayuki Suzuki]] for \"Melancholia\" \u2022 ''Best New Artist'': [[iKon (South Korean band)|iKON]] \u2022 ''Best Song'': [[58th Japan Record Awards#Best Song Award|several]] }}\n|-\n! [[2016 Mnet Asian Music Awards|Mnet Asian Music Awards]]\n|-\n| {{small|''Artist of the Year'': [[BTS (band)|BTS]] \u2022 ''Album of the Year'': ''[[Ex'Act]]'' by [[Exo (band)|Exo]] \u2022 ''Song of the Year'': \"[[Cheer Up (song)|Cheer Up]]\" by [[Twice (band)|Twice]] \u2022 ''Best Music Video'': ''[[Whistle (Black Pink song)|Whistle]]'' by [[BLACKPINK]]}}\n|-\n! [[2016 MTV Video Music Awards|MTV Video Music Awards]]\n|-\n| {{small|''Video of the Year: \"[[Formation (song)|Formation]]\" \u2022 Best Male Video: \"[[This Is What You Came For]]\" \u2022 Best Female Video: \"[[Hold Up (song)|Hold Up]]\" \u2022 New Artist: [[DNCE]]''}}\n|-\n! [[2016 MTV Europe Music Awards|MTV Europe Music Awards]]\n|-\n| {{small|''Best Song: \"[[Sorry (Justin Bieber song)]]\" \u2022 Best Video: \"[[Starboy (song)|Starboy (The Weeknd song)]]\" \u2022 Best Female: [[Lady Gaga]] \u2022 Best Male: [[Shawn Mendes]]''}}\n|-\n! [[The 4th V Chart Awards]] \n|-\n| {{small|''Top Male Artist '': [[Lu Han]] with ''Medals'' \u2022 ''Top Female Artist'': [[Li Yuchun]] with \"\u6df7\u86cb\uff0c\u6211\u60f3\u4f60\" (Idiot, I Miss You) \u2022 ''Top Group'': [[TFBOYS]] with ''Adore'' \u2022 ''Top New Artist'': [[Wang Qing (actor)|Wang Qing]] & [[Feng Jianyu]]}}\n|-\n! [[Rock and Roll Hall of Fame]]\n|-\n| {{small|'''Inductees:''' [[Cheap Trick]] \u2022 [[Chicago (band)|Chicago]] \u2022 [[Deep Purple]] \u2022 [[N.W.A]] \u2022 [[Steve Miller (musician)|Steve Miller]]}}\n|}\n\n==Bands formed==\n{{Div col|colwidth=30em}}\n*[[AOA Cream]]\n*[[Astro (South Korean band)|Astro]]\n*[[BEJ48]]\n*[[Black Pink]]\n*[[Bolbbalgan4]]\n*[[BoybandPH]]\n*[[Boys Generally Asian]]\n*[[CocoSori]]\n*[[Cosmic Girls]]\n*[[Dreamcar]]\n*[[The East Light]]\n*[[Exo-CBX]]\n*[[GNZ48]]\n*[[Gone Is Gone]]\n*[[Gugudan]]\n*[[I.B.I (band)|I.B.I]]\n*[[I.O.I]]\n*[[Imfact]]\n*[[Kard (band)|Kard]]\n*[[KNK (band)|KNK]]\n*[[Lovebites (band)|