]]'''<br>3BC \u2013 AD 68-69}} \n{{tree chart| |!| | | | | | | |!|}}\n{{tree chart| |!| | | | | | | Mat |Mat=[[Salonina Matidia]]<br>68-119}}\n{{tree chart| |!| | | |,|-|-|-|(|}}\n{{tree chart| Had |-| Sab | | Rup |Had='''[[Hadrian]]'''<br>76-117-138 |Sab=[[Vibia Sabina]]<br>80\u2013137 |Rup=[[Rupilia]]<br>87\u2013138}}\n{{tree chart| | | | | | | |,|-|^|-|.|}}\n{{tree chart| | | | | | | Ann | | Fau |v| Ant |Ant='''[[Antoninus Pius]]'''<br>86-138-161 |Fau=[[Faustina the Elder]]<br>100\u2013141 |Ann=[[Marcus Annius Verus (praetor)|Marcus Annius Verus]]}}\n{{tree chart| | | | | | | |!| | | | | |!|}}\n{{tree chart| | | | | | | Mau |-|v|-| Fay |Mau='''[[Marcus Aurelius]]'''<br>121-161-180 |Fay=[[Faustina the Younger]]<br>125\u2013175}}\n{{tree chart| | | | | |,|-|-|-|v|'| | | |}}\n{{tree chart| | | | | Com | | Luc |-| Ver |Com='''[[Commodus]]'''<br>161-180-192 |Luc=[[Lucilla]]<br>148\u2013182 |Ver='''[[Lucius Verus]]'''<br>130-161-169}}\n{{tree chart/end}}\n\n<!-- If anyone knows of a link between the Antonines and the Severans, that would be very useful. -->\n\n==192\u2013235==\nThe emperors from [[Pertinax]] to the beginning of the [[Crisis of the Third Century|Crisis]] can be organised into one large dynasty (see [[Severan dynasty family tree]]), one smaller family and two unrelated emperors.\n\n{{tree chart/start}}\n{{tree chart| Per | | Did |Per='''[[Pertinax]]'''<br>126-192-193 |Did='''[[Didius Julianus]]'''<br>133-193-193}}\n{{tree chart| | | | | |,|-|-|-|-|-|.|}}\n{{tree chart| Sep |v| Dom | | | | Mae | | | | Mac |Sep='''[[Septimius Severus]]'''<br>145-193-211 |Mac='''[[Macrinus]]'''<br>165-217-218 |Dom=[[Julia Domna]]<br>160\u2013217 |Mae=[[Julia Maesa]]<br>165\u2013224| }}\n{{tree chart| |,|-|^|-|.| | | |,|-|^|-|.| | | |!|}}\n{{tree chart| Car | | Get | | Soa | | Jam | | Dia |Car='''[[Caracalla]]'''<br>188-198-217 |Get='''[[Publius Septimius Geta|Geta]]'''<br>189-209-211 |Dia='''[[Diadumenian]]'''<br>r. 218 |Soa=[[Julia Soaemias]]<br>180\u2013222 |Jam=[[Julia Avita Mamaea]]<br>180\u2013235}}\n{{tree chart| | | | | | | | | |!| | | |!|}}\n{{tree chart| | | | | | | | | Ela | | Als |Ela='''[[Elagabalus]]'''<br>203-218-222 |Als='''[[Alexander Severus]]'''<br>208-222-235}}\n{{tree chart/end}}\n\n==235\u2013284, [[Crisis of the Third Century|Crisis of the 3rd Century]]==\nThe emperors during the fifty-year period of the Crisis can be organised into seven families and seven unrelated emperors, although no family held power for more than fifteen years.\n\n{{tree chart/start}}\n{{tree chart| Max | | Gr1 | | Pup | | Bal |Max='''[[Maximinus Thrax]]'''<br>173-235-238 |Gr1='''[[Gordian I]]'''<br>159-238-238 |Pup='''[[Pupienus]]'''<br>178-238-238 |Bal='''[[Balbinus]]'''<br>165-238-238}}\n{{tree chart| | | |,|-|^|-|.}}\n{{tree chart| | | Gr2 | | Ant | | | | Pta | | | | Dec | | | | Tre |Gr2='''[[Gordian II]]'''<br>192-238-238 |Ant=[[Antonia Gordiana]]<br>b. 201                                            |Pta='''[[Philip the Arab]]'''<br>204-244-249 |Dec='''[[Decius]]'''<br>201-249-251 |Tre='''[[Trebonianus Gallus]]'''<br>206-251-253}}\n{{tree chart| | | | | | | |!| | | | | | | | | |,|-|^|-|.| | | |!|}}\n{{tree chart| Aem | | | | Gr3 | | Val | | | | Her | | Hos | | Vol |Gr3='''[[Gordian III]]'''<br>225-238-244 |Her='''[[Herennius Etruscus]]'''<br>227-251-251 |Hos='''[[Hostilian]]'''<br>230-251-251 |Vol='''[[Volusianus]]'''<br>r.  251\u2013253 |Aem='''[[Aemilianus]]'''<br>210-253-253 |Val='''[[Valerian (emperor)|Valerian]]'''<br>200-253-260 }}\n{{tree chart| |,|-|-|-|.| | | | | |!| | | | | | | | | |,|-|-|-|.|}}\n{{tree chart| Clg | | Qui | | | | Gal | | | | Aur | | Tac | | Flo |Gal='''[[Gallienus]]'''<br>218-253-268 |Clg='''[[Claudius Gothicus]]'''<br>213-268-270 |Qui='''[[Quintillus]]'''<br>220-270-270 |Aur='''[[Aurelian]]'''<br>214-270-275 |Flo='''[[Florianus]]'''<br>r. 276 |Tac='''[[Marcus Claudius Tacitus|Tacitus]]'''<br>200-275-276}}\n{{tree chart| |}}\n{{tree chart| Pro | | Car |Pro='''[[Marcus Aurelius Probus|Probus]]'''<br>232-276-282 |Car='''[[Carus]]'''<br>230-282-283}}\n{{tree chart| | | |,|-|^|-|.|}}\n{{tree chart| | | Cai | | Num |Cai='''[[Carinus]]'''<br>r. 283\u2013285 |Num='''[[Numerian]]'''<br>r.  283\u2013284}}\n{{tree chart/end}}\n\n==284\u2013518==\nThe emperors from the founding of the [[Dominate]] in 284, in the [[Western Roman Empire|West]] until 476 and in the [[Eastern Roman Empire|East]] until 518, can be organised into one large dynasty plus ten unrelated emperors. \n\n{{tree chart/start}}\n{{tree chart| | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | Dio |Dio='''[[Diocletian]]'''<br>244-284-305-311}}\n{{tree chart| | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | |!| | | |,|-|-|-|-|-|-|-|.|}}\n{{tree chart| | | | | Sev | | | | Han |v| Eut |v| Max | | Var |-| Gal |v| unk | | uns |Var=[[Galeria Valeria|Valeria]] |Gal='''[[Galerius]]'''<br>260-305-311 |unk=unknown wife |Max='''[[Maximian]]'''<br>250\u2013310<br>r. 286\u2013305, 306\u20138 |Eut=[[Eutropia]]<br>d. 325 |Han=Afranius Hannibalianus |uns=unknown sister |Sev='''[[Flavius Valerius Severus|Severus]]'''<br>r.  306\u2013307}}\n{{tree chart| | | | | | | |,|-|-|-|-|-|'| | | |)|-|-|-|.| | | | | | | |!| | | | | |!|}}\n{{tree chart| | | | | | | The |v| Chl |v| Hel |!| | | Mae |-|-|-|-|-| Vam | | | | Mad |Vam=[[Valeria Maximilla]] |The=[[Flavia Maximiana Theodora|Theodora]] |Mae='''[[Maxentius]]'''<br>278-306-312 |Chl='''[[Constantius Chlorus]]'''<br>250-305-306 |Hel=[[Helena of Constantinople]]<br>250\u2013330 |Mad='''[[Maximinus II|Maximinus]]'''<br>270-311-313}}\n{{tree chart| |,|-|-|-|-|-|-|-|(| | | |!| | | |!|}}\n{{tree chart| Jul | | Lic |-| Cia | | Co1 |v| Fau | | | | Val | | Mar |Cia=[[Flavia Julia Constantia|Constantia]]<br>293\u2013330 |Lic='''[[Licinius]]'''<br>250-308-324-325 |Co1='''[[Constantine I]]'''<br>272-313-337 |Val='''[[Valerius Valens]]'''<br>r.  316\u2013317 |Mar='''[[Martinian (Sextus Martinianus)|Martinian]]'''<br>r.  324 |Fau=[[Fausta]]<br>289\u2013326 |Jul=[[Julius Constantius]]<br>d.  337}}\n{{tree chart| |!